      <processinfo id="aspace_86290d2c8be69e2f8075b535f7c0e5d3">
         <head>Processing Information</head>
         <p>Yale University records are arranged and described at the accession level by the creating office. The University Archives creates collection level descriptive records, but typically does no further arrangement and description at the accession level.</p>  
      </processinfo>
      <scopecontent id="aspace_f1c01f093408b34dfb8a9ba0f5dc5924">
         <head>Scope and Contents</head>
         <p>The records consist of reports and analyses documenting the activities and operations of the Gift Accounting Office, including records for the Campaign for Yale. Also included are printouts of gifts by source, category, and purpose; printouts on pledge information; and a gifts master list.</p>  
      </scopecontent>
      <arrangement id="aspace_d71f4a2a6350ff2d688d70546cbdc990">
         <head>Arrangement</head>
         <p>The records are arranged by accession.</p>  
      </arrangement>
